                <h2>Introduction</h2><hr width=100%>
                With the beginning of the COVID era, many services were disontinued to try and stop the spread of the 
                deadly virus. However, the alternatives to everything were found rather too quickly. For example: cinemas
                were replaced by OTT platforms like netflix, shopping malls were replaced by online shopping platforms
                like amazon, schools and offices were replaced by online meeting platforms, outdoor activities were 
                replaced by video games etc.<br><br>
                But all these alternatives came with inherent flaws, which have cost us too much. Cinemas and shopping 
                malls always meant joyous outings, schools meant a lot more than just studies and video games can 
                never come anywhere near the outdoor sports. So many screens during the pandemic have actually led us 
                into darkness. People are suffering from so many mental diseases, out of which depression, anxiety 
                and stress are just a few names.
                Amongst children and teens; obesity, indigestion, neck pain and insomnia have become extremely common. 
                The diseases with which only senior citizens suffered have now started endangering children.
                
                <br><br><i><b>So, the 
                question we need to ask ourselves is what do we still miss? We are sure that your answer will be a better 
                quality of life.</i></div>
            </div>
